# FFmpeg dual target (web + Tauri)

## Two execution paths

| Target | Mechanism | Files / notes |
|--------|-----------|----------------|
| **Web** | `@ffmpeg/ffmpeg` WASM (multi-thread core), virtual FS | [src/features/video-export/utils/ffmpegWeb.ts](src/features/video-export/utils/ffmpegWeb.ts), assets under `public/ffmpeg-mt`, Vite COOP/COEP for threads |
| **Desktop (Tauri)** | Bundled sidecar `binaries/ffmpeg` via `Command.sidecar` in [`src/shared/utils/tauriFfmpeg.ts`](src/shared/utils/tauriFfmpeg.ts); populate with `bash scripts/download-ffmpeg-sidecars.sh` | Disk paths only — no virtual FS; includes libass for burned-in subtitles |

Never assume a single environment: code that runs in both must branch on capability (Tauri vs browser) and keep I/O shapes explicit.

## Command construction

- Build filter graphs and argv via **`buildFFmpegCommand`** and helpers in [src/features/video-export/utils/ffmpegUtils.ts](src/features/video-export/utils/ffmpegUtils.ts). Avoid ad-hoc string concatenation scattered across components.

## Web virtual FS

- Use `ffmpeg.writeFile` / `ffmpeg.readFile` (or project wrappers) for inputs/outputs in WASM mode.
- Clean up temp virtual paths after runs to avoid memory growth across exports.

## Testing

- **Unit tests** must use the in-memory mock from [src/test/harness/ffmpegHarness.ts](src/test/harness/ffmpegHarness.ts) — do not load real WASM in Vitest for command validation.
- For tracing real command sequences in integration or manual debugging, prefer recording through [src/test/harness/legibility/FFmpegAudit.ts](src/test/harness/legibility/FFmpegAudit.ts) where wired.

## Audio / shell elsewhere

- Some shared audio paths may use Tauri shell with a brew-style binary name — keep naming consistent with [src/shared/utils/audio.ts](src/shared/utils/audio.ts) and platform checks when touching export-adjacent audio.
